components:
  - name: meat
    ingredients:
      - item: ox tail
        mass: 650
      - item: short rib
        mass: 250
      - item: red wine
      - item: beef stock
        optional: true
        note: optionally chicken stock
      - item: thyme
      - item: rosemary
      - item: bay leaf
      - item: green part of leek
    steps:
      - gently sear meat in 150°C pan to golden brown
      - remove meat and reduce red wine in the same pan
      - make bouquet garni of thyme, rosemary and bay, wrapped in green part of leek
      - add beef stock once wine reduced
      - add all to dutch oven, add cartouche, into 160°C oven for 3.5 hours or so
  - name: pomme duchesse
    ingredients:
      - item: potatoes
      - item: salt
      - item: butter
        mass: 30
      - item: egg yolk
        qty: 1
        unit: ea
      - item: pepper
      - item: nutmeg
    steps:
      - roast potatoes at 180°C on salt until soft
      - scoop out insides, rice and tammy sieve
      - melt butter
      - whisk an egg yolk
      - combine potato with butter, egg yolk, pepper and nutmeg
    notes: |
      Should still be stiff enough to survive the oven. Too buttery and it'll bubble.
  - name: mirepoix
    ingredients:
      - item: shallots
      - item: mushrooms
      - item: carrots
      - item: butter
      - item: tomato puree
    steps:
      - dice shallots, mushrooms and carrots
      - sweat down shallots in foaming butter
      - increase heat and add mushroom
      - finally add carrot
      - don't cook too much, it will be in the oven for a while, but do get some colour
      - add tomato puree and cook down some
  - name: sauce / pie filling
    steps:
      - remove meat after braise in oven
      - pour remaining sauce into mirepoix pan
      - get sauce to good consistency
      - add some worcestershire sauce
      - reintroduce meat
  - name: finishing
    ingredients:
      - item: melted butter
    steps:
      - add combined mix to final pot/pan, leave an inch or so at the top
      - pack duchesse on top with domed top
      - use melted butter and spatula to smooth
      - use fork or any old tool with melted butter to texture top surface for browning
      - into 160°C oven for 25 mins or so (check after 20)
